name: Bicycle Crunches
description: Lie on your back and alternate elbow to opposite knee in a pedaling motion.

name: Levitation Crunch
description: Lift your legs and shoulders off the ground and hold the position briefly.

name: Lying Leg Raises
description: Lie on your back and lift your legs up together without bending the knees.

name: Mountain Climbers
description: In plank position, alternate driving your knees toward your chest quickly.

name: Plank
description: Hold a straight-body position supported by forearms and toes.

name: Russian Twists
description: Sit with feet off the ground and twist your torso side to side.

name: Side Bridge Twists
description: Hold a side plank and twist your torso under and back up.

name: Side Planks
description: Hold your body in a straight line on your side supported by one forearm.

name: Sliding Tucks
description: From a plank, slide your feet forward to your chest and back using socks or sliders.

name: Swipers
description: Sit and pass your feet over an object while keeping your hands behind you for support.

name: Bird Dog Rows
description: In a quadruped position, row one dumbbell while keeping the opposite leg extended for balance.

name: DB Reverse Flyes
description: Bend over and raise dumbbells out to the sides to target the upper back.

name: DB Shrugs
description: Lift your shoulders toward your ears while holding dumbbells at your sides.

name: DB Dead Row
description: Perform a row starting from a dead stop at the bottom of the movement.

name: Dumbbell Deadlifts
description: Lower dumbbells to the ground with bent knees and a straight back, then lift back up.

name: Romanian Deadlifts
description: With a slight bend in the knees, lower the dumbbells down your legs while keeping your back straight, then return to standing.

name: Dumbbell Row
description: Bend over and pull the dumbbell toward your waist.

name: Bent-Over Reverse Grip Rows
description: With palms facing forward, bend over and row the dumbbells toward your lower abdomen to target lower lats.

name: Dumbbell Tripod Rows
description: Place one hand on a bench and row a dumbbell with the other hand.

name: Incline Bench Rows
description: Lie face down on an incline bench and row the dumbbells toward your hips.

name: Pull-ups
description: Hang from a bar and pull your chin above the bar.

name: Pullover
description: Lie on your back and bring a dumbbell from overhead to above your chest.

name: Renegade Rows
description: In a plank position, row each dumbbell alternately while maintaining balance.

name: Reverse Snow Angels
description: Lie face down and sweep your arms in a wide arc from hips to overhead, keeping them lifted.

name: Superman
description: Lie face down and lift your arms, chest, and legs off the ground, then lower.

name: Table Rows
description: Lie under a sturdy table or bar and pull your chest toward the surface.

name: Reverse Plank Leg Raises
description: Support your body in a reverse plank and alternately raise one leg at a time, keeping hips lifted to engage the back and glutes.

name: Bodyweight Biceps Curl (using towel or rings)
description: Hang from a towel or rings and curl your body toward the anchor point using your biceps.

name: DB Waiter Curls
description: Hold one dumbbell vertically with both hands under the top plate and curl it up like serving a tray.

name: DB Around‑the‑World Curls
description: Hold a dumbbell by the end; perform a full 360° arc in front of your body, curling through 0–12 o'clock and back down slowly.

name: DB Concentration Curls
description: Sit and curl a dumbbell with your elbow resting on your thigh.

name: DB Cross-Body Hammer Curls
description: Curl each dumbbell across your body toward the opposite shoulder with palms facing in.

name: DB Incline Curls
description: Lie back on an incline and curl dumbbells with full range of motion.

name: DB Preacher Curls
description: Rest your upper arm on an incline bench or chair and curl the dumbbell up.

name: DB Reverse Curls
description: Curl dumbbells with palms facing down to target the brachialis.

name: DB Wall Curls
description: Stand with your back, elbows, and shoulders against a wall and curl the dumbbells without moving your upper arms to isolate the biceps.

name: DB Bicep Curls
description: Lift the dumbbells toward your shoulders by flexing your elbows.

name: DB Reverse Zottman Curls
description: Curl dumbbells up with palms facing down, rotate at the top to palms up, and lower slowly. Focuses on brachialis and forearms.

name: Dumbbell Drag Curls
description: Curl dumbbells while dragging your elbows behind your torso.

name: Hammer Curls
description: Curl dumbbells with palms facing each other.

name: Isometric Curl Hold
description: Hold the dumbbells at a 90-degree curl position to engage the biceps isometrically.

name: Zottman Curls
description: Curl dumbbells up normally, rotate wrists, and lower with palms down.

name: Archer Push-ups
description: Perform push-ups by shifting your weight from side to side, extending one arm while bending the other.

name: Bench Press
description: Lie on a flat surface and press dumbbells upward from your chest.

name: Chest Squeeze Press
description: Press two dumbbells together in front of your chest and push upward while keeping tension between them.

name: Decline Dumbbell Press
description: Lie on a decline bench and press dumbbells upward from your lower chest.

name: Dumbbell Bench Press
description: Lie down and press dumbbells from chest level to above your shoulders.

name: Dumbbell Flyes
description: With arms extended, lower dumbbells out to the sides and bring them back up.

name: Explosive Push-ups
description: Push up forcefully enough to lift your hands off the ground, then land softly and repeat.

name: Incline Dumbbell Flyes
description: Lie on an incline bench and lower the dumbbells out to the sides, then bring them together over your chest.

name: Incline Dumbbell Press
description: Lie on an incline bench and press dumbbells from chest level to above your shoulders.

name: Push-up to Dumbbell Row
description: Do a push-up holding dumbbells, then row one dumbbell at a time to your waist after each push-up.

name: Push-ups
description: Lower and raise your body using your arms in a plank position.

name: Wide Push-ups
description: Do push-ups with your hands placed wider than shoulder-width to target the chest more.

name: Deadlifts
description: Lower dumbbells while keeping legs slightly bent and back straight.

name: Dumbbell Lunges
description: Step forward into a lunge position while holding dumbbells.

name: Dumbbell Squats
description: Hold dumbbells and squat down until thighs are parallel to the ground.

name: Hyperextensions
description: Bend forward at the waist and lift your torso back to alignment.

name: Leg Extensions
description: Straighten your knee from a seated position using your legs.

name: Lunges
description: Step forward and bend both knees to 90 degrees, then return.

name: Squats
description: Lower your hips from a standing position and rise back up.

name: Arnold Press
description: Rotate dumbbells from front to overhead press position.

name: DB Bent-Over Lateral Raise
description: Bend forward and raise dumbbells out to the sides to target rear delts.

name: DB Cuban Press
description: Start with dumbbells at 90-degree elbows, rotate upward, then press overhead.

name: DB Front Raises
description: Lift dumbbells forward until they reach shoulder height.

name: DB Lateral Raises
description: Lift dumbbells out to the sides up to shoulder height.

name: DB Over Head Press
description: Press dumbbells vertically overhead from shoulder level.

name: DB Rear Delt Rows
description: Bend forward and row dumbbells outward to target rear delts.

name: DB Scoop Press
description: Lift dumbbells in an upward and inward scoop motion overhead.

name: DB Upright Rows
description: Pull dumbbells upward along the body to chest height, keeping elbows above hands.

name: DB Z Press
description: Sit on the floor with legs extended and press dumbbells overhead without back support.

name: DP Hip Huggers
description: Lift dumbbells slightly forward and up close to the body.

name: Dumbbell Shoulder Press
description: Press dumbbells upward from shoulder height until arms are extended.

name: Elevated Pike Push-ups
description: Place feet on an elevated surface and perform pike push-ups for added resistance.

name: Handstand Push-ups
description: In a handstand position against a wall, lower your body and press back up.

name: Pike Push-ups
description: With hips elevated, lower your head between your hands and push back up.

name: Wall Walks
description: Start in a push-up position and walk your feet up the wall while walking hands toward it.

name: 1 Arm Over Head Triceps
description: Extend one arm overhead with a dumbbell, lowering and lifting behind the head.

name: Close Grip Bench Press
description: Press dumbbells from chest level with hands close together.

name: Cobra Push-Ups
description: Push-up variation with elbows close to body and hips low.

name: DB Incline Powerbombs
description: Press dumbbells overhead at an incline to target triceps.

name: Diamond Push-Ups
description: Place hands close together and perform a push-up to target triceps.

name: Dumbbell Tricep Extensions
description: Lift a dumbbell overhead and lower behind the head, then extend arms.

name: JM Press
description: Lower dumbbells toward the forehead, then press upward.

name: Lying Triceps Extensions
description: Lie down and extend dumbbells from forehead to straight arms.

name: Triceps Kickbacks
description: Extend your arm back from a bent-over position to contract triceps.
